replyContent: Thanks for your rating. Internet access is required for crash reporting. If you do not opt in to crash reports, no connections are made at any time. Clipboard history in Clipper has always run as a foreground service, which did not require a permission before Android 9. As the new update targets Android 9, the foreground permission was added.

It is an excellent app with one very serious flaw. I use this app almost every day, multiple times per day. I use it most times that I have more than one sentence to compose. I use it in conjunction with other apps, and to compose text that will get sent via web but for which I will have no other copy (e.g. consumer feedback). I used the app to write this review! I would easily give it five stars except that it has no auto-backup feature, or auto save-to-draft, in case you get interrupted during a long edit, or your battery goes out, etc. You will lose all the text entered during that edit. The app could very easily have a feature where it continually saved to a draft or an auto-restore file every few seconds. I would then immediately and rightfully give the app 5 stars. I have written to the developer twice about this. Once a few years ago, and again a few months ago. No response from developer.

This is the best app I have found in a long time. It's perfect and got 
everything, I would ask for in a clip out/copying [Ctrl+C & Ctrl+V, 
functionality] manager application. For example; You can store "a ton of" 
clip outs. You can make your own lists as well and save your copying 
"forever". For example if you want to save unique signs, like: ☣, ♫ or some 
emoticons, like: ヽ(ヅ)ノ, ツ. There is also a function to create dynamic 
clippings: - Copy the current date. You access the Clipper+ in the Android 
drop-down menu, the access to all your clipping is fast and easy. You sync 
your data to your Google Account. I love this function, then I have no 
problem to replace my phone in the future. Or sync my 2 Android devices, so 
both have the "up to date clippings". I would like to see this in Windows 
also (there is a way to get access to the clippings through the web 
browser). I can't find any tools that works as awesome as, Clipper Plus 
with Sync, in Windows 10. So if you guys create a similar app for Windows, 
I'm going to invest in it also. Clipper Plus with Sync is priceless. / 
Thanks

I have contacted the author of the application. Whose advice was not useful.  2 - when trying to paste from the list I have learned that not all Android applications allow to select a clip from the clipboard (all allow to paste the latest one though). One of the tools that does allow it is the standard text message application of Android (4.1). However I have noticed that the list available for me there is not the one I see in the clipboard.
